<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> The Schubert can be seen briefly on <i>Hereafter</i>, the transcription of Bruckner's <a href="/wiki/Symphony_No._8_(Bruckner)" title="Symphony No. 8 (Bruckner)">8th symphony</a> Gould alludes to in an article in <i>The Glenn Gould Reader</i> where he deprecates its "sheer leger-line unplayability"; the Strauss opera playing can be seen in one of the <a href="/wiki/Humphrey_Burton" title="Humphrey Burton">Humphrey Burton</a> conversations and is referred to by almost everyone who saw him play in private.</li>
